events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Darius Garland didn't show any rust. He shined just like an All-Star.
headlines.shortLinkText: All-Star Garland drops 27 in return, leads Cavs past Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 36 points, Nikola Vucevic added 18 points, 15 rebounds and eight assists, and the Chicago Bulls handed the Charlotte Hornets their sixth consecutive loss, 121-109 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, Vucevic lead Bulls past struggling Hornets 121-109

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 27 points and 16 rebounds, Fred VanVleet made six 3-pointers and added 21 points, and the Toronto Raptors beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 117-98 on Wednesday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam, Raptors top Thunder 117-98 for seventh straight win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Several opponents have said the Utah Jazz can’t defend when big man Rudy Gobert isn’t cleaning up their mistakes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz shut down Warriors 111-85 to stop 9-game win streak

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Struggling to find a silver lining after a flurry of trades depleted their roster, the Trail Blazers got some encouragement against the Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons has 29 and Blazers rally for 107-105 win over Lakers

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 30 points, Domantas Sabonis had 22 points and 14 rebounds in his Kings debut and Sacramento pulled away late to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 132-119 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis' double-double leads Kings past Timberwolves 132-119
